		-- 1.3.6.1.4.1.3715.100.5.1.5
		hmtsRegistrationStretchThreshold OBJECT-TYPE
			SYNTAX Integer32
			UNITS "percent"
			MAX-ACCESS read-write
			STATUS current
			DESCRIPTION
				"If a large number of transponders are registering at the same time, it
				may be necessary to extend the registration window. This object defines
				the threshold when this stretching should be performed. During registration,
				collisions are unavoidable, causing corrupted packets.
				By comparing the number of totally received bytes to the number of bytes
				belonging to correctly received packets can be used as an indicator.
				This object defines the threshold for this indicator. If the threshold is
				exceeded, the registration window duration is be doubles."
			::= { hmtsMIB 5 }

		
